In case there are non-existing/missing breeding stocks for which accountability could not be established despite exhaustion of all diligent efforts, we recommended the following courses of actions:
The Head of the Agency cause the conduct of an investigation to determine the last known location where the breeding stock were issued, person accountable, circumstances of the loss, and the persons responsible for the loss, among others;
If accountability/responsibility over these assets was identified after investigation, demand shall be made from the accountable personnel to pay the cost thereof;
The Accounting Unit shall be furnished the certified copy of the investigation report and demand letter to be used as basis to recognize the asset and to set up the corresponding receivables from the concerned accountable officer/personnel; and
If accountability/responsibility over the non-existing/missing breeding stocks could not be pinpointed after investigation, authority for derecognition thereof from the books of accounts may be requested from the COA and pending the grant of authority by the latter, the said asset shall remain in the books of accounts with proper disclosure in the notes to financial statements.

